title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1992-12-11
lineage: SBD DAT master > DAT/1 > CDR > iMac > SHN
description: Cold Rain & Snow, Wang Dang Doodle, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Stagger Lee, Cassidy, Deal Iko Iko, Looks Like Rain, Eyes Of The World-> Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Corrina Corrinaaaaaaa, shake it babe! If this one dont get you fired up nothing will. A+ sound, top five 92 show. Many a night was spent in Clemson, SC partying down with this show in the background. Other highlights include LL Rain, Eyes, Cassidy, Aiko.......

Corrina . Great sound  & mix , good crowd ....a mild "Eyes" starts the second set into Corrina , though everytime I've loved the chant-beat~intro to Corrina , always left with the feeling of  wanting  more developement , intertwining rythmic riffs and syncopated jams lacing it more . But you can't always get what you want . A nice show , I'll give it 3 stars , so just settle back & enjoy this relaxed ride . The sound is crystal clear in the 'ol Dome, you'll love the "Phil Zone" that gets cankin' in Sugar Mag...nice drummin too.

A Prelude to a Run of Spirited Shows Good recording. Good remastering. Good performance.
No appreciable sound anomalies. Solid, well-played. Lots of Vince coming of age. A polished, professional sound, but, of course, not so polished that it hath not blackening flame.
Great sound, uneven mix Keys are too high in the mix.  Weir's guitar and bass are a little low.  Drums are also too loud, but hey, it's a soundboard straight to DAT so not bad for on the fly
Solid Dead Good Feel. Sound Typical of late 90's DAT's. Corina stands out definitely.Too bad there is no way of giving 2 1/2 stars straight down the middle show.
